NOTE     "synopsis": "Introduction to the Vajrasattva Fire Puja Meditation\nVen. Khenpo Tsewang Dongyal Rinpoche\n\nNYC New Years Eve Dakini Puja of H.H. Dudjom Rinpoche\u2019s Khandro Thugtik and New Year's Vajrasattva and Vajrakilaya Practices with Ven. Khenpo Tsewang Rinpoche!\n\nDecember 31, 2018\nJanuary 1, 2019\n\n222 Bowery Street, New York City\n(between Prince and Spring)\n\nVen. Khenpo Tsewang Dongyal Rinpoche joined the PBC NYC Sangha for a wonderful New Years Eve Dakini Puja, which included a lovely dinner and fundraising party for the PBC Monks and Nuns in Sarnath, India! Dakini practice was according to the Khandro Thugtik practice and tsok ceremony from the terma of His Holiness Dudjom Rinpoche, and the meditation practice included the following sadhana prayer books:\n\nPBC Daily Prayers\nKhandro Thugtik of HH Dudjom Rinpoche\nDharmapala prayers\nStainless King\nWhite Umbrella\nLion-Faced Dakini\nGreat Cloud of Blessings\n\n. . . Followed by the Annual New Year Day Vajrasattva & Vajrakilaya Practice with Khenpo Tsewang Rinpoche on January 1, 2019.\n\nMorning Vajrasattva fire puja practice: 9:00am\u201312:30\nAfternoon Vajrakilaya and Dharmapala practice with tsok ceremony: 2:30\u20135:30pm\n\nWe began the New Year with Vajrasattva and Vajrakilaya! This Vajrasattva fire puja practice mainly focuses on pacifying negativities and obstacles while increasing prosperity, joy, longevity, peace, and realization. It is a terma of Terdak Lingpa. Vajrakilaya is the embodiment of all the buddhas\u2019 activities and is one of the most famous practices of the Nyingma school. Practicing on Vajrakilaya removes our obstacles, eases the flow of Dharma activity, and reveals our buddha-nature. The Vajrakilaya practice is a terma of Tsasum Lingpa.\n\nSadhana Prayer Books we used:\n\nMorning Practice:\n\nDaily Prayers \u2013 Opening and Dedication\nMinling Vajrasattva Fire Puja\nRiwo Sang Chod\n\nAfternoon Practice:\n\nDaily Prayers \u2013 Opening and Dedication\nVajrakil